<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1779645-can-this-be-read-as-a-stand-alone-my">Can this be read as a stand-alone? My library only has this one book by David Eddings.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1779645'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F18884.Polgara_the_Sorceress">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1779645-can-this-be-read-as-a-stand-alone-my">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1779645-can-this-be-read-as-a-stand-alone-my">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6666905-liz"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6666905-liz">Liz</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;m late, but I wanted to answer for anyone else wondering about this.<br/><br/>While I personally discovered Eddings with this book and loved it so much I move<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'm late, but I wanted to answer for anyone else wondering about this.<br /><br />While I personally discovered Eddings with this book and loved it so much I moved on to read all their other epic fantasy novels. I do NOT recommend it as a stand-alone... <br /><br />I don't think the prologue/first chapter can make much sense to anyone who asn't read the Belgariand and the Malloreon... It's a major SPOILER for the whole series because, while Belgarath the Sorcerer and Polgara the Sorceress are seen as "prequels", they take place AFTER all the other books. <br />They're seen as "prequels" because the narrators are telling the story of what happened before the series to the other characters from the series. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1158153" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1158153&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1779645-can-this-be-read-as-a-stand-alone-my%2Fanswers%2F1158153-i-m-late-but-i-wanted">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

