<div id="review_818343603" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/818343603" />
    <a title="Adam Knight" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22098973-adam-knight"><img alt="Adam Knight" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610935857p2/22098973.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/818343603?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adam Knight" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adam Knight" href="/user/show/22098973-adam-knight">Adam Knight</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer818343603" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5581476506511276902">Disliked. Loved the Belgariad. Loved the Mallorean. Suffered through &quot;Belgarath the Sorcerer&quot; despite it being the extended version of history we already knew. Having to go through it all onceagain in Polgara&apos;s tale was nigh on insufferable. As this book went along I began to find traces of the &quot;smug voice&quot; that has ruined Eddings&apos; work past this realm for me.<br/><br/>For hardcore Eddings fans only.</span>
  <span id="freeText5581476506511276902" style="display:none">Disliked. Loved the Belgariad. Loved the Mallorean. Suffered through "Belgarath the Sorcerer" despite it being the extended version of history we already knew. Having to go through it all onceagain in Polgara's tale was nigh on insufferable. As this book went along I began to find traces of the "smug voice" that has ruined Eddings' work past this realm for me.<br /><br />For hardcore Eddings fans only.</span>
